### **Material Information Summary (Betashares ETF Changes)**  

#### **Key Changes to Betashares Global Income Leaders ETF (INCM):**  
- **New Index & Objective:** Effective **5 August 2025**, the fund will track the **S&P World Ex-Australia High Dividend Aristocrats Select Index** (previously Nasdaq Global Income Leaders Index).  
- **Rebranding:** Renamed to **Betashares S&P Global High Dividend Aristocrats ETF** (ASX code remains **INCM**).  
- **Fee Reduction:** Management costs drop from **0.45% p.a.** to **0.39% p.a.** (no recoverable expenses).  
- **Index Methodology Shift:** Focuses on companies with **10+ years of stable/increasing dividends**, targeting lower volatility and turnover.  
- **Portfolio Impact:** Expected holdings: **100–200 stocks**, sector/regional diversification aligned with global markets.  

#### **No Material Changes Identified for Other ETFs (ASIA, RBTZ, QLTY).**  

**Trading Implication:** Investors in **INCM** should review portfolio alignment post-index transition (effective 5 August 2025).  

*—Extracted per ECM analyst guidelines—*
